    "5 This definition fits exactly the diagnostic example provided above and many of the descriptions that can be found in the medical literature about the medical process of reasoning: for example, Aliseda (2006) claims that \"abduction is a reasoning process invoked to explain a puzzling observation\" (Aliseda, 2006, p. 28).",
    "Another important characteristic of abduction 6, following Peirce (cf.",
